rComments: By far one of my best profs so far. His lectures are super interesting, plus he's always willing to reexplain and answer questions. We had a semester long project and he did an amazing job making sure we had all the ressources and feedback needed to succeed. Can't say enough good things about him, I'd highly recommend his class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Simon is an incredible prof and if you land on one of his classes, consider yourself lucky. All I can say
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: He's literally the best man - all i gotta say!

Simon is honestly one of the best profs I had the chance to have. I met with him almost every week to discuss the project. The project is quite difficult if you have no previous research experience but I would recommend to take this course with him regardless. Super nice, great lectures and super accessible outside of class.

You guys, he truly is THE BEST PROF UOTTAWA HAS TO OFFER!!! You can tell he really cares about us & always adapts the material to the rhythm of the class. He made stats really interesting and fun!! 10000/10!! I absolutely recommend!

Étant donnée que je suis un étudiant en 4ème qui rédige ca thèse. Je vous suggère fortement de prendre ce cours avec ce prof. Ces travaux et son matériel vont vous servirez à long terme si c'est pas à court terme.

Meilleur professeur que j'ai eu à l'Université jusqu'à maintenant. Il prend le temps de déstresser l'environnement de test et de nous expliquer les objectifs du cours plutôt que de nous "enculer avec des détails pour passer un test et avoir une note". Je recommande à tous. Merci Simon!
super bon prof, gentil et énergétique. je recommande fortement, il est attentif et cest clair quil veut le meilleur pour ses étudiants
Un prof fantastique! Il est super gentil et il a notre réussite à coeur- Je lui recommande fortement!

The fact that he's giving his classes in English is a gift for students like me who cannot speak/understand French. Best prof is a label that he embodies. He's very caring and changes his teaching if and when he finds necessary. He's very patient and has the ability to make stats fun to learn. All in all, I'm thankful and I hope he knows it.
BEST. PROF. EVER. Il est là pour aider ses étudiants à bien comprendre et à réussir. Prend de son propre temps pour faire des rencontres avec ses étudiants pour les aider.

Ce prof est facilement le meilleur prof que j'ai eu à luniversité. Il a su rendre un cours absolument plate comme la méthodologie quantitative fun et engagent juste par son attitude. I didnt know those words could go together. 11/10 would recommend

Super bon enseignant. Il est super drôle et encourage la participation des élèves. Il s'assure de la compréhension de ses étudiants et enseigne super bien la matière. Un de mes préféré dans mon BAC, je le recommande à tous.

Un super bon prof! Il est toujours accessible en dehors de la classe surtout si tu as des questions par rapport aux projets. Il est prêt à aider et à donner des explications claires quand tu en as de besoin. Je le reprendrai!

M. Beaudry est l'un des meilleurs profs que j'ai eu durant cette session. Il est toujours là pour aider ses étudiants et fait tout en son pouvoir pour les motiver en sachant bien que les statistiques ne sont pas évidentes pour plusieurs étudiants en communication. Il est dynamique et ça parait qu'il apprécie le travail qu'il fait. Je le recommande!

Un prof qui fait tout pour aider ses étudiants. Clairement le meilleur prof que jai eu. Cest aussi le premier cours où le prof et le TA sont sur la même longueur donde (ils devraient être nominés pour le meilleur duo Prof-TA si ça lexiste ou pour le meilleur prof et le meilleur TA). +++, les deux sont super stylés et beaux! Bref, Simon  God!

Très très bon professeur! Il était super gentil et toujours là pour aider mais son cours c'était tellement dur et horrible! Etant déjà nul en maths et stats j'ai rien compris mais il veut absolument qu'on passe le cours ! Je le recommande comme prof mais pas son cours du tout !
Amazing, gives you all the tools you need to succeed. Wish every prof was like him!!
His classes are very enjoyable, and the grading criteria is very clear. Step-by-step instructions on how to get an A!

I'm not the biggest fan of stats, but he managed to make it my favourite class of the semester. He's passionate, clear and makes sure everyone is on the same page before moving on to the next topics. I enjoyed everything about this class, the morning classes, the assignments and the labs! Simon and Phil AKA the dynamic duo!

I hate stats (still do) but I looked forward to his lectures. He clearly loves the material and makes the content easier to understand. He's willing to go through subjects and exams to explain errors and make things clear. I would definitely recommend him, Simon's great!

Simon is a great prof! I hate stats (still do) but I looked forward to his lectures. He clearly loves the material and makes the content easier to understand. He's willing to go through subjects and exams to explain errors and make things clear. I would definitely recommend him!
Dr Beaudry is clearly very passionate about teaching. He tries to make sure everyone understands before moving to the next subject.

Meilleur prof au monde. Super gentil, super chaleureux, super compréhensif. Il s'assure que tout le monde comprenne la matière avant d'avancer plus loin. Il inclu les élèves (participation) et encourage le travail d'équipe. Super relaxe comme prof. Rien à dire de mauvais!

He's super passionate and knowledgeable about the course content. Always makes sure that students are on the same page about a subject before moving on to the next. Course is relatively tough, but he does his best to teach it in a way that even the worst students are able to understand what this or that means and what they're supposed to do. 10/10

Teaches how to do research very well, step by step explanations for methodology and writing.  Always around to help out and give tips.  A lot of papers and a lot of work for each paper but overall gives a good feel for what future research is going to be like.

Simon est probablement le meilleur prof que j'ai eu la chance d'avoir depuis le début de mon bac. En plus d'être super gentil, il prend le temps de bien expliquer, il est dynamique et veut la réussite de tout le monde. Le fait que lui et son assistant sont cutes est un extra.

je recommande Simon à tout le monde ! C'est le meilleur prof que j'ai eu durant mon bac ! Il enseigne un cours que j'ai trouvé plus thecnique qu'à l'habitude mais sa personnalité et son approche rendent le cours beaucoup plus facile !

Un des meilleurs prof que j'ai eu. Il sait garder l'attention de la classe et il tient au succès de ces étudiants. Il a réussit à rendre un cours de méthode de recherche très plaisant ce que je croyais impossible. Je reprendrais ce prof n'importe quand.

With all honesty, Simon Beaudry is by FAR the best prof I have ever had. He is an excellent teacher and is very dynamic. It shows that he wants everyone to succeed. He is super down to earth and cares about every student (to the point where he knows each student by name). If you can try your best to have this prof, you wont regret it ! :)

Caring prof. If you don't understand something and go to see him after class, he'll explain it in 10 ways if he has to, he'll explain until you understand. A very step-by-step prof, which lowers stress levels as he explains in detail everything that needs to be completed. Also, participate in his classes, it makes everything much more fun!! :)

This is the worst of the 40+ profs i've had until now... He has double standards and uses terms he made up in his office with some students to describe statistics. He will get you lost pretty quickly. Always uses made up words to teach exam content, and only addresses a small portion of his class (those who could actually go to his office hours)

He's a really good and fun teacher. He is stimulating, caring , understanding, dynamic. He enjoys teaching and it shows. He wants to help and accommodate you as best as he can. He will stay with for hours , if he has to. We went to visit some labs and even went out for a drink and nachos on the last class on him ! He's on of the best teacher i had!

Définitivement le MEILLEUR PROF que j'ai eu dans mon bac jusqu'à maintenant! Explique vraiment bien la matière, exercises pratique en classe, très chaleureux, sortie de classe, nous avons été déjeuner tous ensemble au dernier cours. Les test représentent bien la matière. Si vous prenez stat avec Simon, vous n'aurai pas de difficulté dans le cours.
C'est un des meilleurs professeurs que j'ai eu, le cours est difficile, une chance que j'avais ce professeur comme enseignant.

Amazing! He saved my semester. He somehow made  Méthodes Quantitatives  an enjoyable class. He is always available to answer questions. He truly wants to help his students succeed. You can tell he cares.

exceptional both as a person and as a professor and mentor Hes always there for his students, is super thoughtful & understanding of the million other things weve got going on & is here to help & support you Having him as a teacher goes deeper than just having an exceptional teacher hes a fundamentally good person with his values in the right place

Probably the only professor I know who remembers the names of his students. It makes you feel like more than a number and accepts to look over your work if you disagree with the grade you got. Very helpful and very respected by students.
Professeur très beau ;) ! Il explique très bien les stats et c'est quand même facile avoir des bonnes notes avec de l'étude.
Amazing pedagogue, devoted to his craft. Makes the terrifying topic of statistics for social sciences as painless as it could possibly be by listening to what the students need.

he's a great teacher, teaching a horrible class. as awful as the class is, he tries really hard to make sure everyone understands the subject. he gives many examples and is always taking peoples feedback into consideration.
Un des profs les plus marquants de mon Bac. Il est un enseignant née! Il explique de la matière difficile comme les stats avec brio! Merci Simon!

Fantastic prof, more than willing to spend time after class answering questions. Statistics can be really brutal and too calculation heavy but he tries to make it practical and easy to understand by applying it to relatable examples and walking you through it. Would recommend him as a prof for sure.

Le meilleur professeur que j'ai eu dans mes années de BAC. Toujours là pour ses élèves. Explique très bien la matière, si on ne comprend pas il va nous aider dans ses heures de bureau ou les labs. Un cour de statistiques n'est pas toujours motivant, mais Simon sait comment motiver ses élèves et rendre le cour palpitant!!

I mean stats is a tough class & I wouldn't have passed if it weren't for Simon! He's really nice, caring, & passionate about what he  teaches. I loved coming to every one of his classes. Because of his will to help all his students, I actually like stats! And he's HOT. I mean a hottie teaching stats? AND NO TEXTBOOK! He is the Greek God of stats!3

Not the best experience I've had. Professor seems like a nice guy but isn't very clear when explaining. Wants students to understand the material on a deeper level and this shows in the midterms multiple choice questions which are random and tough (some answers haven't been said directly in class). Would not recommend.

HORROR. This professor spends the semester beating around the bushes as means to explain every concept you will see in the class. Nothing is straightforward with him and so nothing gets accomplished. Willing to push due dates and lots of office hours to make up for bad teaching. DO NOT take him for stats! Good grades are better than good laughs.

Cares about his students. Very helpful, make a meeting with him if you have questions!! Less experience teaching wise and his teaching skills feel very fresh. Final project was crystal clear, easy A if you make the link between the labs and his teachings. Try him out!
awesome

class was useless, we weren't tested on anything he taught. The giant project was super confusing since he and the TA did not agree on guidelines nor a grading scheme. Worst experience for a class ever!

Hands down the best prof I've ever had. I had him for Stats I and II and he made me fall in love with stats. He explains clearly,expectations are crystal clear. His midterms are 100% representative of what youve learnt in class. He regrades assignments when he realises the class is lost or pushes back deadlines. He will meet at any time to clarify.

Prof super gentil et proche de ses élèves. Même si j'ai été déçu de ma note, je sais qu'il a tout fait pour m'aider et qu'il est toujours disposé à ses étudiants. J'ai poché mon examen final, quand je suis allé le voir il a tout fait pour me rajouter des points. Il est sympathique, explique bien et comprend la critique.
Great teacher, he really cares about his students and will do anything to help. If you have to take stats II you should really take it with him!

Super clear about expectations. Very engaged in his material and is a wonderful lecturer. Gets the class laughing a lot. Need to prepare for the midterm. Doesn't use a lot of math in his stats courses (more theory). Overall a great prof
Amazin prof, very clear, helpfull definitly take his class :)
Loved him! Made every class interesting, and was very helpful in making sure everyone understood.

Excellent professeur. Il connaissait les noms de tous après quelque cours seulement. Excellent tant en classe qu'en personne. J'ai réellement aimé le cours de métho, tandis que la plupart des gens ont vécu une expérience terrible avec d'autre professeurs. Choisissez ces cours si vous pouvez!

AMAZING PROF!! If you can take him, he's a great prof, always available to help you out, only have assignments for the class, no midterm, the final is a paper that you need to hand in. Super flexible and easy going, super approachable and nicest prof I've had in my two years!
Excellent professor! Very clear expectations and lectures were very enjoyable. Extremely helpful throughout the semester. By far the best prof I've had at uOttawa.

He's a great teacher! He's extremely helpful and always takes time to answer our questions, both in class and outside of class period. He's respectful to all the students and treats everyone nicely. He's also really funny in class and often tells jokes! Take him and you won't regret it!

Best teacher I've had so far in university. Very patient, explains everything if you ask, super nice. No exams or tests (although he said he might include some next year), just a big research assignment divided into 4 parts (the textbook is basically a guide for your assignment). I came into this class already hating it, but I actually enjoyed it!
I am taking his class this semester and he is the best teacher ive had at university
One of the best profs I've had, very helpful and always willing to make time for questions and meetings, treats you as a prof should - like a person and not a number; DEFINITELY take his class
He was amazing! I love him, and he was super cute. A really kind hearted, and smart person. I wouldn't have taken this course with anyone else!

Greeeat prof. If you're taking Research Methods don't take it with any other prof, especially if you're looking to write a thesis in psychology at any point, it's the best preparation. Also very clear what you need to do to get a high grade. You basically carry out a research project during the semester and get a ton of feedback. Even had fun!

Nice guy, easy to approach. Sounds like Jerry Seinfeld. Gets a little snippy during lectures when he thinks he's teaching things we should already know, but one on one he's very patient. Was sometimes hard to meet with - busy guy. I think they piled too much on him this semester. No exams, expensive textbook.
